High throughput sequencing yielded about 9.9 million reads (
Fig. 3
). Quality filtering discarded 86 955 (0.87%) sequences. No reads related to coronavirus could be detected with EDGE’s taxonomy classification module, but BLAST alignments (98–100% and 90–95%, for respectively query coverage and identity percentage) revealed 2 small coronavirus contigs (210 bp and 271 bp) from one sample. Those contigs have been determined as being parts of replicase polyprotein 1ab.

